ylor, [https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2009/sep/08/religion-islam-tablighi-jamaat What is the Tablighi Jamaat?], The Guardian, 8 September 2009.\n* {{Cite journal |last=Stern |first=Jessica |title=Pakistan's Jihad Culture. |journal=Foreign Affairs |volume=79 |issue=6 |pages=115\u201326 |year=2000 |url=https://www.foreignaffairs.com/articles/asia/2000-11-01/pakistans-jihad-culture |doi=10.2307/20049971 |jstor=20049971 }}\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{commons category}}\n{{wikiquote}}\n* [http://www.delhimarkaz.com/?m=1/ Tablighi Jamaat Official Website]\n{{Tablighi Jamaat}}\n{{IslamismSA|state=collapse}}\n\n{{Coord|31|15|25|N|74|13|22|E|display=title|region:PK_type:city(31592)_source:dewiki}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1927 establishments in India]]\n[[Category:Tablighi Jamaat|*]]\n[[Category:Islamic organisations based in India]]\n[[Category:Sunni Islamist groups]]\n[[Category:Islamic organizations established in 1926]]\n[[Category:Deobandi]]\n", "name_user": "Dr.azharuddin", "label": "safe", "comment": "population of tableeghi members", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tablighi_Jamaat"}
{"title_page": "Daniel Auteuil", "text_new": "{{short description|French actor and director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Daniel Auteuil\n| image        = File:Daniel Auteuil redux.jpg\n| caption      = Daniel Auteuil in 2011\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1950|01|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[French Algeria]]\n| spouse       = {{Plainlist|\n* Anne Jousset (?\u2013?)\n* {{Marriage|[[Emmanuelle B\u00e9art]]|1993|1995}}\n* {{Marriage|Aude Ambroggi|22 July 2006}}\n}}\n| partner      = [[Marianne Denicourt]]\n| children     = 3; including [[Aurore Auteuil]]\n| years_active = 1974\u2013present\n| occupation   = Actor, film director, screenwriter\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Auteuil''' ({{IPA-fr|danj\u025bl ot\u0153j}}; born 24 January 1950) is a French actor and director who has appeared in a wide range of film genres, including period dramas, romantic comedies, and crime thrillers.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\">{{cite news|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil Biography |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/2912/Daniel-Auteuil/biography |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref> In 1996 he won the [[Best Actor Award (Cannes Film Festival)|Best Actor Award]] at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] together with Belgian actor [[Pascal Duquenne]]. He is also the winner of two [[C\u00e9sar Award for Best Actor|C\u00e9sar Awards for Best Actor]], one in 1987 as Ugolin Soubeyran in ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' and ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' and one for his role in ''[[Girl on the Bridge]]''. For his role in ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' he also won the [[BAFTA Award]] for Best Actor in a Supporting Role.<ref name=\"nytimes-awards\">{{cite news|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil Awards |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/2912/Daniel-Auteuil/awards |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref> Auteuil is considered one of France's most respected actors.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/><ref name=\"allmovie\">{{cite web|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil |publisher=AllMovie |url=http://www.allmovie.com/artist/daniel-auteuil-p2912 |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nDaniel Auteuil was born on 24 January 1950 in [[Algiers]], [[French Algeria]], the son of opera singers.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/> He grew up in [[Avignon]] and [[Nancy, France|Nancy]], [[France]].<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/> He began his acting career in musical comedy and made his film debut in 1972.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/>\n\nAuteuil's starring role in the [[historical fiction|historical drama]] film ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' (1986) and its sequel ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' (1986) brought him international recognition.  Auteuil has since become one of the best-known, best-paid and most popular actors in France. Through his appearances in films including  the [[swashbuckler film|swashbuckler]] ''[[Le Bossu (1997 film)|Le bossu]]'' (1997), the [[comedy]] ''[[The Closet (2001 film)|The Closet]]'' (2001), the [[romantic comedy]] ''[[After You...]]'' (2003), the [[Thriller film|thriller]] ''[[Cach\u00e9 (film)|Cach\u00e9]]'' (2005) and the [[comedy film|comedy]] ''[[My Best Friend (2006 film)|My Best Friend]]'' (2006), he has since gained greater international recognition.\n\nIn 2013, Auteuil was selected as a member of the main competition jury at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|last=Saperstein |first=Pat |title=Nicole Kidman, Christopher Waltz, Ang Lee Among Cannes Jury Members | work=Variety | publisher=Reed Business Information |date=23 April 2013 |url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/nicole-kidman-christopher-waltz-ang-lee-among-cannes-jury-members-1200410650/ |accessdate=23 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nAuteuil has two daughters: [[Aurore Auteuil]] with his former partner, Anne Jousset, and Nelly from a ten-year relationship with actress [[Emmanuelle B\u00e9art]], his co-star in the films ''[[A Heart in Winter]]'' and ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' (1986). He married Aude Ambroggi, a Corsican sculptor, on 22 July 2006 in [[Porto-Vecchio]], [[Corsica]].\n\n==Selected filmography==\n\n===As actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Title\n! width=\"15%\"| Role\n! width=\"20%\"| Director\n|- \n| 1974\n| ''[[L'Agression]]''\n| Natacha's boyfriend\n| [[G\u00e9rard Pir\u00e8s]]\n|-\n|1975\n| ''[[Attention les yeux !]]''\n| Alex\n| [[G\u00e9rard Pir\u00e8s]]\n|-\n|1977\n|''[[Monsieur Papa (1977 film)|Monsieur Papa]]''\n| D\u00e9d\u00e9\n| [[Philippe Monnier]]\n|-\n|1977\n|''[[Rendez-vous en noir]]''\n|Inspecteur Camaret\n|Claude Grinberg\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1979\n|''[[Us Two (film)|Us Two]]''\n|''a rascal'' \n|[[Claude Lelouch]]\n|-\n|''[[Heroes Are Not Wet Behind the Ears]]''\n|''Jean-Bernard''\n| [[Charles Nemes]]\n|-\n|1980 \n|''[[Les sous-dou\u00e9s]]''\n|''B\u00e9bel''\n|[[Claude Zidi]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1981\n|''[[Les hommes pr\u00e9f\u00e8rent les grosses]]''\n|''Jean-Yves''\n|[[Jean-Marie Poir\u00e9]] \n|-\n|''[[Les Sous-dou\u00e9s en vacances]]''\n|''B\u00e9bel''\n|Claude Zidi\n|-\n|''[[Clara et les Chics Types]]''\n|''Mickey''\n|Jacques Monnet\n|-\n|1982\n|''[[Pour cent briques, t'as plus rien...]]''\n|''Sam''\n| [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1984 \n|''{{Interlanguage link multi|Les Fauves (film)|fr|3=Les Fauves (film)|lt=Les Fauves}}''\n|''Christopher Bergham''\n| Jean-Louis Daniel\n|-\n|''[[Asphalt Warriors]]''\n|''Inspecteur Vincent''\n| [[Sergio Gobbi]]\n|-\n|''[[P'tit Con]]''\n|''Jeannot''\n| [[G\u00e9rard Lauzier]]\n|-\n|1985 \n|''{{Interlanguage link multi|Palace (film)|fr|3=Palace (film, 1985)|lt=Palace}}''\n|''Lucien Molard''\n| [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1986\n|''[[Jean de Florette]]''\n|rowspan=2|''Ugolin''\n|rowspan=2|[[Claude Berri]] \n|-\n|''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources