frag\u00e9s]]''\n|''Jean-Louis Brochard''\n|[[David Charhon]]\n|-\n|''[[Au nom de ma fille]]''\n|''Andr\u00e9 Bamberski''\n|[[Vincent Garenq]]\n|-\n|''[[The Confessions (film)|The Confessions]]''\n|''Daniel Roch\u00e9''\n|[[Roberto And\u00f2]]\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Le Brio]]''\n|''Pierre Mazard''\n|[[Yvan Attal]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[:fr:R\u00e9mi sans famille (film)|R\u00e9mi Alone in the World]]''\n|''[[Sans Famille|Vitalis]]''\n|[[:fr:Antoine Blossier|Antoine Blossier]]\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[La Belle \u00c9poque (film)|La Belle \u00c9poque]]''\n|\n|[[Nicolas Bedos]]\n|}\n\n===As filmmaker===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! rowspan=2 width=\"33\"| Year\n! rowspan=2| Title\n! colspan=2| Credited as\n! rowspan=2| Notes\n|-\n! width=65 |Director\n! width=65 |Screenwriter\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2011\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The Well-Digger's Daughter (2011 film)|The Well-Digger's Daughter]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Marius (2013 film)|Marius]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Fanny (2013 film)|Fanny]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2018\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Le proverbe]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|}\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" width=\"90%\"\n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Award\n! width=\"20%\"| Category\n! width=\"40%\"| Film\n! width=\"5%\"| Result\n|-\n|1987 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' || {{won}}\n|-\n|1987 || [[BAFTA Award]] || Best Actor in a Supporting Role || ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' || {{won}}\n|-\n|1988 || [[Moli\u00e8re Award]]s || Best Actor || ''[[Double Inconstancy]]'' (''La Double Inconstance'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1989 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Quelques jours avec moi]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1991 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Lacenaire (film)|Lacenaire]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1991 || [[Moli\u00e8re Award]]s || Best Actor || ''[[Les Fourberies de Scapin]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1993 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[A Heart in Winter]]'' (''Un c\u0153ur en hiver'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1993 || [[European Film Award]] || Best Actor || ''[[A Heart in Winter]]'' || {{won}}\n|-\n|1994 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[My Favorite Season]]'' (''Ma saison pr\u00e9f\u00e9r\u00e9e'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1995 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[La Separation|La S\u00e9paration]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1997 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[The Eighth Day (1996 film)|The Eighth Day]]'' (''Le huiti\u00e8me jour'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|1998 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Le Bossu (1997 film)|Le Bossu]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|2000 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Girl on the Bridge]]'' (''La Fille sur le pont'') || {{won}}\n|-\n|2001 || [[Lumi\u00e8res Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[Sade (film)|Sade]]'' || {{won}}\n|-\n|2003 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[The Adversary (film)|The Adversary]]'' (''L'Adversaire'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|2004 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[After You...]]'' (''Apr\u00e8s vous...'') || {{nom}}\n|-\n|2005 || [[C\u00e9sar Awards]] || Best Actor || ''[[36 Quai des Orf\u00e8vres (film)|Department 36 (36, quai des Orf\u00e8vres)]]'' || {{nom}}\n|-\n|2005 || [[European Film Award]] || Best Actor || ''[[Cach\u00e9 (film)|Cach\u00e9]]'' || {{won}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Commons category}}\n* {{IMDb name|0000809|Daniel Auteuil}}\n* {{AllRovi person|2912|Daniel Auteuil}}\n\n{{Daniel Auteuil}}\n{{Navboxes\n|title = Awards for Daniel Auteuil\n|list =\n{{BAFTA Award for Best Supporting Actor 1985-2009}}\n{{Prix d'interpr\u00e9tation masculine 1980\u20131999}}\n{{C\u00e9sar Award for Best Actor}}\n{{David di Donatello for Best Foreign Actor}}\n{{European Film Award for Best Actor}}\n{{Golden Goblet Award for Best Actor}}\n{{Lumi\u00e8res Award for Best Actor}}\n}}\n{{C\u00e9sar Awards presidents}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Auteuil, Daniel}}\n[[Category:1950 births]]\n[[Category:20th-century French male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century French male actors]]\n[[Category:Algerian emigrants to France]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Cours Florent]]\n[[Category:BAFTA winners (people)]]\n[[Category:Best Supporting Actor BAFTA Award winners]]\n[[Category:Best Actor C\u00e9sar Award winners]]\n[[Category:Cannes Film Festival Award for Best Actor winners]]\n[[Category:David di Donatello winners]]\n[[Category:European Film Award for Best Actor winners]]\n[[Category:Best Actor Lumi\u00e8res Award winners]]\n[[Category:French male film actors]]\n[[Category:French male stage actors]]\n[[Category:French male television actors]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:People from Algiers]]\n[[Category:Pieds-Noirs]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|French actor and director|bot=PearBOT 5}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2012}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name         = Daniel Auteuil\n| image        = File:Daniel Auteuil redux.jpg\n| caption      = Daniel Auteuil in 2011\n| birth_date   = {{Birth date and age|1950|01|24|df=y}}\n| birth_place  = [[French Algeria]]\n| spouse       = {{Plainlist|\n* Anne Jousset (?\u2013?)\n* {{Marriage|[[Emmanuelle B\u00e9art]]|1993|1995}}\n* {{Marriage|Aude Ambroggi|22 July 2006}}\n}}\n| partner      = [[Marianne Denicourt]]\n| children     = 3; including [[Aurore Auteuil]]\n| years_active = 1974\u2013present\n| occupation   = Actor, film director, screenwriter\n}}\n\n'''Daniel Auteuil''' ({{IPA-fr|danj\u025bl ot\u0153j}}; born 24 January 1950) is a French actor and director who has appeared in a wide range of film genres, including period dramas, romantic comedies, and crime thrillers.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\">{{cite news|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil Biography |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/2912/Daniel-Auteuil/biography |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref> In 1996 he won the [[Best Actor Award (Cannes Film Festival)|Best Actor Award]] at the [[Cannes Film Festival]] together with Belgian actor [[Pascal Duquenne]]. He is also the winner of two [[C\u00e9sar Award for Best Actor|C\u00e9sar Awards for Best Actor]], one in 1987 as Ugolin Soubeyran in ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' and ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' and one for his role in ''[[Girl on the Bridge]]''. For his role in ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' he also won the [[BAFTA Award]] for Best Actor in a Supporting Role.<ref name=\"nytimes-awards\">{{cite news|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil Awards |newspaper=The New York Times |url=https://www.nytimes.com/movies/person/2912/Daniel-Auteuil/awards |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref> Auteuil is considered one of France's most respected actors.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/><ref name=\"allmovie\">{{cite web|last=Marx |first=Rebecca Flint |title=Daniel Auteuil |publisher=AllMovie |url=http://www.allmovie.com/artist/daniel-auteuil-p2912 |accessdate=13 August 2014}}</ref>\n\n==Life and career==\nDaniel Auteuil was born on 24 January 1950 in [[Algiers]], [[French Algeria]], the son of opera singers.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/> He grew up in [[Avignon]] and [[Nancy, France|Nancy]], [[France]].<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/> He began his acting career in musical comedy and made his film debut in 1972.<ref name=\"nytimes-bio\"/>\n\nAuteuil's starring role in the [[historical fiction|historical drama]] film ''[[Jean de Florette]]'' (1986) and its sequel ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' (1986) brought him international recognition.  Auteuil has since become one of the best-known, best-paid and most popular actors in France. Through his appearances in films including  the [[swashbuckler film|swashbuckler]] ''[[Le Bossu (1997 film)|Le bossu]]'' (1997), the [[comedy]] ''[[The Closet (2001 film)|The Closet]]'' (2001), the [[romantic comedy]] ''[[After You...]]'' (2003), the [[Thriller film|thriller]] ''[[Cach\u00e9 (film)|Cach\u00e9]]'' (2005) and the [[comedy film|comedy]] ''[[My Best Friend (2006 film)|My Best Friend]]'' (2006), he has since gained greater international recognition.\n\nIn 2013, Auteuil was selected as a member of the main competition jury at the [[2013 Cannes Film Festival]].<ref name=\"variety\">{{cite web|last=Saperstein |first=Pat |title=Nicole Kidman, Christopher Waltz, Ang Lee Among Cannes Jury Members | work=Variety | publisher=Reed Business Information |date=23 April 2013 |url=https://variety.com/2013/film/news/nicole-kidman-christopher-waltz-ang-lee-among-cannes-jury-members-1200410650/ |accessdate=23 April 2013}}</ref>\n\nAuteuil has two daughters: [[Aurore Auteuil]] with his former partner, Anne Jousset, and Nelly from a ten-year relationship with actress [[Emmanuelle B\u00e9art]], his co-star in the films ''[[A Heart in Winter]]'' and ''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]'' (1986). He married Aude Ambroggi, a Corsican sculptor, on 22 July 2006 in [[Porto-Vecchio]], [[Corsica]].\n\n==Selected filmography==\n\n===As actor===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" \n|-\n! width=\"5%\"| Year\n! width=\"20%\"| Title\n! width=\"15%\"| Role\n! width=\"20%\"| Director\n|- \n| 1974\n| ''[[L'Agression]]''\n| Natacha's boyfriend\n| [[G\u00e9rard Pir\u00e8s]]\n|-\n|1975\n| ''[[Attention les yeux !]]''\n| Alex\n| [[G\u00e9rard Pir\u00e8s]]\n|-\n|1977\n|''[[Monsieur Papa (1977 film)|Monsieur Papa]]''\n| D\u00e9d\u00e9\n| [[Philippe Monnier]]\n|-\n|1977\n|''[[Rendez-vous en noir]]''\n|Inspecteur Camaret\n|Claude Grinberg\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1979\n|''[[Us Two (film)|Us Two]]''\n|''a rascal'' \n|[[Claude Lelouch]]\n|-\n|''[[Heroes Are Not Wet Behind the Ears]]''\n|''Jean-Bernard''\n| [[Charles Nemes]]\n|-\n|1980 \n|''[[Les sous-dou\u00e9s]]''\n|''B\u00e9bel''\n|[[Claude Zidi]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1981\n|''[[Les hommes pr\u00e9f\u00e8rent les grosses]]''\n|''Jean-Yves''\n|[[Jean-Marie Poir\u00e9]] \n|-\n|''[[Les Sous-dou\u00e9s en vacances]]''\n|''B\u00e9bel''\n|Claude Zidi\n|-\n|''[[Clara et les Chics Types]]''\n|''Mickey''\n|Jacques Monnet\n|-\n|1982\n|''[[Pour cent briques, t'as plus rien...]]''\n|''Sam''\n| [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|1984 \n|''{{Interlanguage link multi|Les Fauves (film)|fr|3=Les Fauves (film)|lt=Les Fauves}}''\n|''Christopher Bergham''\n| Jean-Louis Daniel\n|-\n|''[[Asphalt Warriors]]''\n|''Inspecteur Vincent''\n| [[Sergio Gobbi]]\n|-\n|''[[P'tit Con]]''\n|''Jeannot''\n| [[G\u00e9rard Lauzier]]\n|-\n|1985 \n|''{{Interlanguage link multi|Palace (film)|fr|3=Palace (film, 1985)|lt=Palace}}''\n|''Lucien Molard''\n| [[\u00c9douard Molinaro]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1986\n|''[[Jean de Florette]]''\n|rowspan=2|''Ugolin''\n|rowspan=2|[[Claude Berri]] \n|-\n|''[[Manon des Sources (1986 film)|Manon des Sources]]''\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Quelques jours avec moi]]''\n|''Martial Pasquier''\n|[[Claude Sautet]] \n|-\n|1989\n|''[[Romuald et Juliette]]''\n|''Romuald Blindet''\n|[[Coline Serreau]]\n|- \n|1990\n|''[[Lacenaire]] [[The Elegant Criminal]]\n|''Lacenaire\n|[[Francis Girod]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1991\n|''[[A Heart in Winter]]''\n|''St\u00e9phane''\n|Claude Sautet\n|-\n|''[[My Life Is Hell]]''\n|''Abargadon''\n|[[Josiane Balasko]]\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[My Favorite Season]]''\n|''Antoine''\n|[[Andr\u00e9 T\u00e9chin\u00e9]] \n|-\n|1993 \n|''[[La Reine Margot (1994 film)|La Reine Margot]]'' \n| ''[[Henry IV of France|Henri de Bourbon]]''\n|[[Patrice Ch\u00e9reau]] \n|-\n|1994\n|''[[La S\u00e9paration]]''\n|''Pierre''\n|[[Christian Vincent (director)|Christian Vincent]]\n|-\n|1995\n|''[[A French Woman]]''\n|''Louis''\n|[[R\u00e9gis Wargnier]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1995\n|''[[Thieves (1996 film)|Thieves]]''\n|''Alex''\n|Andr\u00e9 T\u00e9chin\u00e9\n|-\n|''[[Sostiene Pereira]]''\n|''Dr. Cardoso''\n|[[Roberto Faenza]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|1996\n|''[[The Eighth Day (1996 film)|The Eighth Day]]''\n|''Harry''\n|[[Jaco Van Dormael]] \n|-\n|''[[Lucie Aubrac (film)|Lucie Aubrac]]''\n|''Raymond''\n|Claude Berri \n|-\n|1997\n|''[[On Guard (1997 film)|On Guard]]''\n|''Lagard\u00e8re''\n|[[Philippe de Broca]] \n|-\n|1998\n|''[[Girl on the Bridge]]''\n|''Gabor'' \n|[[Patrice Leconte]]\n|-\n|rowspan=4|1999 \n|''[[The Lost Son (film)|The Lost Son]]''\n| ''Xavier Lombard''\n|[[Chris Menges]]\n|-\n|''[[The Escort (Mauvaise passe)]]''\n| ''Pierre''\n|[[Michel Blanc]]\n|-\n|''[[The Widow of Saint-Pierre]]''\n| ''Jean''\n|[[Patrice Leconte]]\n|-\n|''[[The Closet (2001 film)|The Closet]]''\n|''Fran\u00e7ois Pignon''\n|[[Francis Veber]] \n|-\n|2000 \n|''[[Sade (film)|Sade]]''\n|''Marquis de Sade''\n|[[Beno\u00eet Jacquot]] \n|-\n|2001 \n|''[[Vajont (film)|Vajont]]''\n|''Alberico Biadene''\n|Renzo Martinelli\n|-\n|2002\n|''[[The Adversary (film)|The Adversary]]''\n|''Jean-Marc Faure''\n|[[Nicole Garcia]] \n|-\n|rowspan=2|2003\n|''[[Rencontre avec le dragon]]''\n|''Guillaume de Montauban''\n|H\u00e9l\u00e8ne Angel \n|-\n|''[[After You...]]''\n| ''Antoine Letoux''\n|[[Pierre Salvadori]] \n|-\n|rowspan=2|2004 \n|''[[36 Quai des Orf\u00e8vres (film)|36 Quai des Orf\u00e8vres]]''\n|''L\u00e9o Vrinks''\n|[[Olivier Marchal]] \n|-\n|''[[Strange Crime]]''\n| ''Daniel''\n|[[Roberto And\u00f2]] \n|-\n|rowspan=2|2005 \n|''[[Cach\u00e9 (film)|Cach\u00e9]]''\n| ''Georges Laurent''\n|[[Michael Haneke]] \n|-\n|''[[To Paint or Make Love]]''\n|''William Lasserre''\n|[[Arnaud Larrieu]] and [[Jean-Marie Larrieu]] \n|-\n|rowspan=3|2006\n|''[[The Valet]]''\n|''Pierre Levasseur''\n|[[Francis Veber]]\n|-\n|''[[My Best Friend (2006 film)|My Best Friend]]''\n|''Fran\u00e7ois Coste''\n|[[Patrice Leconte]]\n|-\n|''[[Napoleon and Me]]''\n|''[[Napoleon]]''\n|[[Paolo Virz\u00ec]]\n|-\n|2007\n|''[[Conversations with My Gardener]]''\n|''Dupinceau'' \n|[[Jean Becker (director)|Jean Becker]]\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2008 \n|''[[The Last Deadly Mission]]''\n|''Schneider''\n|[[Olivier Marchal]]\n|-\n|''[[15 ans et demi]]''\n|''Philippe Le Tallec''\n| Fran\u00e7ois Desagnat & Thomas Sorriaux\n|-\n|2009\n|'' [[Je l'aimais]]'' \n|''Pierre''\n|[[Zabou Breitman]]\n|-\n|2011\n|''[[The Well-Digger's Daughter (2011 film)|The Well-Digger's Daughter]]''\n|''Pascal Amoretti''\n|Daniel Auteuil\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2012\n|''[[The Lookout (2012 film)|The Lookout]]''\n|''Mattei''\n|[[Michele Placido]]\n|-\n|''[[Blood from a Stone]]''\n|''Georges Pierret''\n|[[Jacques Maillot]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2013\n|''[[Jappeloup]]''\n|''Serge Durand''\n|[[Christian Duguay (director)|Christian Duguay]]\n|-\n|''[[Marius (2013 film)|Marius]]''\n|''C\u00e9sar''\n|Daniel Auteuil\n|-\n|''[[Fanny (2013 film)|Fanny]]''\n|''C\u00e9sar''\n|Daniel Auteuil\n|-\n|rowspan=2|2015\n|''[[Entre amis]]''\n|''Richard''\n|[[Olivier Baroux]]\n|-\n|''[[Nos femmes]]''\n|''Paul''\n|[[Richard Berry (actor)|Richard Berry]]\n|-\n|rowspan=3|2016\n|''[[Les Naufrag\u00e9s]]''\n|''Jean-Louis Brochard''\n|[[David Charhon]]\n|-\n|''[[Au nom de ma fille]]''\n|''Andr\u00e9 Bamberski''\n|[[Vincent Garenq]]\n|-\n|''[[The Confessions (film)|The Confessions]]''\n|''Daniel Roch\u00e9''\n|[[Roberto And\u00f2]]\n|-\n|2017\n|''[[Le Brio]]''\n|''Pierre Mazard''\n|[[Yvan Attal]]\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[:fr:R\u00e9mi sans famille (film)|R\u00e9mi Alone in the World]]''\n|''[[Sans Famille|Vitalis]]''\n|[[:fr:Antoine Blossier|Antoine Blossier]]\n|-\n|2019\n|''[[La Belle \u00c9poque (film)|La Belle \u00c9poque]]''\n|\n|[[Nicolas Bedos]]\n|}\n\n===As filmmaker===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n! rowspan=2 width=\"33\"| Year\n! rowspan=2| Title\n! colspan=2| Credited as\n! rowspan=2| Notes\n|-\n! width=65 |Director\n! width=65 |Screenwriter\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2011\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[The Well-Digger's Daughter (2011 film)|The Well-Digger's Daughter]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Marius (2013 film)|Marius]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2013\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Fanny (2013 film)|Fanny]]''\n| {{yes}}\n| {{yes}}\n|\n|-\n| align=\"center\" | 2018\n| align=\"left\"| ''[[Le proverbe]]''\n| 